The application uses Solid technology to enable people to create their own "personal online data warehouse", also known as POD.
This may include lists, to-do lists, calendars, music libraries, and other personal and professional tools.
It's like Google Drive, Microsoft Outlook, Slack and Spotify all running from the same browser at the same time.
What's unique about personal online repositories is that it's entirely up to the user to decide who gets access to their data.
The company calls this "implementing the right of individuals to self-determination over their data".
John Bruce, CEO of Inrupt, said the company's mission is to provide the resources, processes and skills to make Solid accessible to everyone.
